President Obama issued a statement expressing his gratitude for Representative Jim McDermott's 40 years of service to the people of Washington State. McDermott has been instrumental in passing laws that provided healthcare to unemployed and low-income individuals in the state, making Washington the first in the nation to do so. The President acknowledged McDermott's efforts in being a voice for vulnerable constituents and stated that families across America are better off because of his advocacy. President Obama wished McDermott all the best in his future endeavors.